I think sometimes studios (particularly Lucasfilm!) can be TOO cautious about spoilers. I think the marketing for a movie like The Last Jedi hurt its reception among, particularly, die-hard Star Wars fans. The level of secrecy led to many people expecting a much different film than the one we got, questions we expected to be answered that were never even brought up in the movie itself. As a result, it felt like a bit of a letdown to learn that Rey is no one special, we were stupid for ever caring about Snoke, Luke never left his hermit island, Phasma is actually a chump who loses all the time and by the way she's dead now, etc.
Trailers help you get excited for the film! It kind of whets your appetite for things you're really excited to see, and can help you decide if it's worth seeing at all.
